news.title: Maharashtra govt starts demolition drive against 800 illegal structures in Malang Gad
news.para: A forest department official, however, said that at present action has only been taken against illegal commercial shops built in the region and no houses were demolished.

news.title: Global capability centres drive office leasing in Jan-June 2024: Report
news.para: Bengaluru had the highest share of GCC leasing, at 39%, followed by Pune at 20%, while Hyderabad and Chennai at 17% and 11%, respectively, during Jan-Jun 2024.

news.title: Whiteland Corporation to invest Rs 5,600 crore to develop Westin Residences in Gurugram
news.para: The total investment for the project is estimated around Rs 5,600 crore, which includes construction cost Rs 5,000 crore while the land cost is Rs 600 crore. The topline of the project is pegged at Rs 15,000 crore.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government aims to complete eight lakh houses by March 2025
news.para: The minister reviewed the progress of housing units taken up under PM Awas Yojana scheme in different housing colonies in the state with the officials in the secretariat on Wednesday.

news.title: Marico’s Priyanjali Mariwala buys apartment for Rs 65 crore in Mumbai’s BKC
news.para: She bought this apartment spread over nearly 8,300 sq ft on the first floor of super-premium residential tower Signature Island from Starlight Systems, a part of the project’s developer Sunteck Realty.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues notices to 38 builders, ask them to conduct surveys of societies
news.para: The order comes after plaster chunks fell off balconies of two residential societies — Paras Dews in Sector 106 and Signature Global Solera in Sector 107 — on Thursday.

news.title: House prices in UK fall by 0.2% in June 2024: Halifax
news.para: "This continued stability in house prices - rising by just +0.4% so far this year - reflects a market that remains subdued, though overall activity has been recovering," Amanda Bryden, head of mortgages at Halifax, said.

news.title: Foreign investors infuse $3.1 billion in Indian real estate in first half of 2024: JLL
news.para: In complete contrast, another property consultant Colliers India, earlier this week, reported a 6 per cent decline in total institutional investment in real estate at USD 3,523.6 million during the first half of 2024 as against USD 3,764.7 million in the year-ago period.

news.title: Two officials suspended for failing to stop illegal sand mining in Maharashtra’s Beed
news.para: The action against Purushottam Sudhakar Andhale (mandal adhikari) and Kiran Prabhakar Dandhe (talathi) came after senior officials found signs of rampant illegal sand mining near a river basin in Georai taluka, he said.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet asks MMRDA to consider clearing Rs 1,700 crore debt owed by MMOPL
news.para: In March 2024, MMOPL signed a debt settlement agreement with the lenders, committing to pay Rs 1,700 crore as one-time settlement of its entire debt.

news.title: L&DO awaits housing ministry approval for converting leasehold properties to freehold in Delhi
news.para: Queries sent to the housing and urban affairs ministry went unanswered, though sources said there was a probability that the ministry would take a call on the issue soon.

news.title: Town & country planning department changes zones of six plots in North Goa
news.para: The TCP department has used Section 39A to tweak the Regional Plan for Goa-2021 and the Outline Development Plan (ODP) of Calangute-Candolim, Planning Area-2025.

news.title: DDA asks Dwarka’s sector 19B housing scheme allottees to settle final payment by Aug 28
news.para: DDA claims these dwelling units are now available for physical possession and the allottees are required to finalise the payment by Aug 28 without interest or by Sept 28 with interest at the rate of 10% per annum.

news.title: Ludhiana: Consumer commission penalises Glada for not giving possession of plot
news.para: Complainant Sushma Lata Bansal of Urban Estate Phase Two, Patiala, said she was allotted a residential plot measuring 95 square yards under the 80-20 scheme on a freehold basis through draw of lots held on October 14, 2019.

news.title: BMC can spare five acres of Mulund octroi land for Dharavi redevelopment
news.para: At the time, BJP politicians, including deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis, party candidate from Mumbai North East Mihir Kotecha and former MP Kirit Somaiya, had stressed that they would not allow the relocation of Dharavi residents to Mulund.

news.title: Experion Developers acquires 7.81-acre land in Gurugram for Rs 400 crore
news.para: The wholly owned Indian subsidiary of Singapore's Experion Holdings Pte Ltd had in the last one-and-a-half years acquired five plots worth Rs 2,100 crore, mainly in Gurugram, where it is in the process of launching new projects.

news.title: Raymond to demerge real estate business, list it on exchanges
news.para: The standalone operational revenue of the real estate division stood at Rs 1,592.65 crore in the last fiscal, accounting for 24 per cent of the total revenue of Raymond Ltd.

news.title: Delhi HC sets aside Punjab & Sind Bank's decision to withdraw Rs 120 crore OTS given to Ambience
news.para: The HC said that it is well settled that OTS offer, its acceptance and the sanction letter constitute a sufficient contract. Thus, the Punjab and Sind Bank, which is a nationalized bank and an instrumentality of the State, cannot act arbitrarily or whimsically in matters of contract

news.title: Average mortgage rate in USA rise to 6.95% in July 2024
news.para: When rates rise they can add hundreds of dollars a month in costs for borrowers. The elevated mortgage rates have been a major drag on home sales, which remain in a slump dating back to 2022.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto rise by 4.2% in June 2024
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales rose by 4.2% in June from May, according to Toronto Regional Real Estate Board (TRREB) data. Average home prices increased by 1.8% to C$1.13 million ($830,000), the highest since December, while new listings were up 9.3%.
